name: r-smurf
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.1.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-smurf
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/smurf_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/smurf/smurf_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: eb0d3764321760e9ab6da26575c9136cef96cd73324e8b9a51209fb0f46f2959

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  skip: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
    - r-matrix
    - r-rcolorbrewer
    - r-rcpp >=0.12.12
    - r-rcpparmadillo >=0.8.300.1.0
    - r-catdata
    - r-glmnet >=4.0
    - r-mgcv
    - r-speedglm
    - libblas
    - liblapack
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-mass
    - r-matrix
    - r-rcolorbrewer
    - r-rcpp >=0.12.12
    - r-rcpparmadillo >=0.8.300.1.0
    - r-catdata
    - r-glmnet >=4.0
    - r-mgcv
    - r-speedglm

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('smurf')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('smurf')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://gitlab.com/TReynkens/smurf
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: Implementation of the SMuRF algorithm of Devriendt et al. (2021) <doi:10.1016/j.insmatheco.2020.11.010> to fit generalized linear models (GLMs) with multiple types of predictors via regularized maximum likelihood.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
